---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro'
---
<BaseLayout title="BridgeAIChat Troubleshooting" description="Fix common BridgeAIChat install and runtime issues.">
  <section class="surface">
    <div class="eyebrow">Troubleshooting</div>
    <h1>Common failures in the beta path.</h1>
    <p class="lede">
      Most first-run issues come from missing local prerequisites, unreachable gateways, or AI CLI problems on the
      agent device itself rather than from the chat UI.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="section-gap grid two">
    <div class="card stack">
      <div class="eyebrow">Connection</div>
      <h2>Device does not appear online</h2>
      <ul class="list tight">
        <li>Check that the gateway is running and reachable at the configured Tailscale URL</li>
        <li>Confirm the agent is pointed at <code>ws://.../agent</code>, not just the bare host</li>
        <li>Restart the agent after editing <code>agent.yaml</code></li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="card stack">
      <div class="eyebrow">Tooling</div>
      <h2>Tool binary not found</h2>
      <ul class="list tight">
        <li>Make sure the configured <code>cmd</code> exists on the agent device</li>
        <li>Use an absolute path if the service environment does not inherit your interactive shell PATH</li>
        <li>Test the configured CLI directly in the terminal before testing from the web UI</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="card stack">
      <div class="eyebrow">Claude</div>
      <h2>Claude replies never arrive</h2>
      <ul class="list tight">
        <li>Check that <code>direct: true</code> is set for the claude tool in <code>agent.yaml</code> — without it, short responses silently time out</li>
        <li>Check that <code>--dangerously-skip-permissions</code> is in both <code>args</code> and <code>continue_args</code> — without it, Claude blocks on a permission prompt waiting for stdin that never arrives; you will receive Claude's "grant permission" text as the reply instead of an actual response</li>
        <li>Run <code>claude -p "hi"</code> on the agent device directly to rule out login or quota issues</li>
        <li>If you see auth or limit errors there, BridgeAIChat cannot fix them — resolve them on the device first</li>
        <li>Switch to Codex temporarily if you want to keep testing while Claude quota is exhausted</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="card stack">
      <div class="eyebrow">Runtime</div>
      <h2>tmux is missing</h2>
      <ul class="list tight">
        <li>tmux is required for Codex and any tool that does not set <code>direct: true</code></li>
        <li>Claude with <code>direct: true</code> does not use tmux — you can run Claude-only agents without tmux installed</li>
        <li>If you are using Codex, install tmux before starting the agent: <code>brew install tmux</code> or <code>apt install tmux</code></li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
